Agencies of the URB

Student Culinary Council
The Student Culinary Council is a free, monthly forum open to all students that brings students together with George Mason’s Dining Administration to discuss all things campus dining.

Co-led by the Undergraduate Representative Body’s Dining Liaison in partnership with Mason Dining. Attendees can learn about upcoming initiatives, ask questions, and share feedback on everything from meal plans and dining halls to the retail locations across campus.

Whether you have suggestions, concerns, or simply want to stay informed, the Student Culinary Council is your opportunity to help shape the future of dining at George Mason.



Student Parking Board
The Student Parking Board is comprised of currently enrolled Mason students, including a Chairman who is elected by Board members. The Board is responsible for hearing student parking appeals and is the second level of appeals. The Board is also responsible for developing parking initiatives to best satisfy the needs of fellow Patriots.

Members are always open to suggestions and feedback on how they can best serve the student body, so feel free to send an email to sg@gmu.edu!


